headline: These Stocks Are Moving the Most Today: Rivian, Ford, Super Micro, Zoom, Semtech, Intel, Dell, CrowdStrike, and More
summary: Rivian receives a loan of up to $6.6 billion from the U.S. government to boost electric-vehicle production, shares of Ford and General Motors fall after President-elect Donald Trump announces his tariff plans, and Super Micro gives back some sharp gains from Monday. Dell and CrowdStrike are scheduled to report earnings Tuesday.
